    "SD1.5 +Self-Cross +ISAC (Ours) +InitNO\"A photo of two horses\" SD1.",
    "5 +Self-Cross +ISAC (Ours) +InitNO \"A photo of a dog and a sheep\" Figure 1.",
    "Importance of instance-level control for multi-object generation.",
    "Existing text-toimage diffusion models (e.g., SD1.5 [1]) and prior training-free guidance methods [2,3] still suffer from count failures (missing or merged instances) and semantic mixing (attributes spilling across objects), whereas ISAC's instance-first design yields the correct number of instances with clearly separated semantics.",
    "IntroductionText-to-image (T2I) diffusion models [1,[4][5][6][7] now produce strikingly realistic images from text prompts."
